Massive electrification of our means of transport and industrial processes also raises major challenges in terms of energy efficiency, economic cost and environmental impact. Developing electric motors that are more efficient with higher power density, lighter and consuming less materials has become a key technological lock.

ğŸ”‹ improve the system efficiency by making motor downsizing more accessible, while guaranteeing the same peak performances, leading to less energy consumption over the operating cycle with a smaller motor more optimised for the most frequently reached operating points;

Solar is no longer an â€œalternativeâ€ â€“ it is now the most cost-effective source of power on the planet. What we need is the political will to scale it up! Employees can help drive this shift by encouraging their companies to be clean energy leaders. Credit for the background image: @mikehankin." -------------- Hello, I'm Laure. I'm a full time climate activist. It's ok, don't get scared ! My purpose is to guide and empower people who work on the inside of large companies to find meaningful ways to take climate action through the lens of their job - no matter what this job is. I do this because: â¤ Climate change is the defining challenge of our time â¤ We need to act like the cavalry is not coming. We cannot afford to wait for someone else to solve this for us. I am someone else. â¤ I want to be able to tell my children that I showed up and did everything I could On this platform, I share my personal views on how and why (most) companies are falling short of what is required to address the climate crisis - and what can be done about it. I call out greenwashing, but I don't want to throw anyone under the bus. This is about finding ways to do better, and most importantly, do what is required (aka, aligned with the science) I am always up for a chat (but no cold outreach about your latest solution on how AI agents will 10x my business please!) You can reach me at laure.legros@workforclimate.org
